      <div class="fv-title">At Peak, Equal. Across a Career, Messi.</div>
      <p class="fv-text">In terms of pure talent and absolute peak level, the two are essentially tied — a draw that no honest analysis can resolve. But when the comparison widens to cover careers, sustained excellence at the highest level, statistical output adjusted for era, and the ability to define what it means to be the best in the world across two decades, the balance tips toward Messi. It tips — it does not collapse. Maradona remains the more dramatic case: the player who produced the most extraordinary moments, who carried more with less, who played in conditions that would have broken almost anyone else. The fact that he was not the better player across a career is simply a reflection of circumstances — not of what he was capable of when he had the ball at his feet, and the world was watching.</p>
